snippet: The European Union said it would finance projects worth about $68 million in Moldova, a former Soviet republic that is prepared to sign an association agreement with the European bloc amid protests from Moscow.
abstract: European Union says it will finance projects worth roughly $68 million in Moldova; former Soviet republic is prepared to sign association agreement with European bloc amid protests from Moscow.
lead_paragraph: The European Union said it would finance projects worth about $68 million in Moldova, a former Soviet republic that is prepared to sign an association agreement with the European bloc amid protests from Moscow.
